                <head>256. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On February 3, 1959, French Ambassador Hervé Alphand, British Ambassador Sir
                        <persName corresp="#p_CSH1">HAROLD CACCIA</persName>, and Deputy Under
                    Secretary <persName corresp="#p_MRD1">Robert Murphy</persName> discussed China
                    and Korea, including Sino-Soviet relations, the recent Taiwan Strait crisis, and
                    the question of recognition. A memorandum of the conversation, which was one of
                    a series of tripartite talks on various issues, is in Department of State,
                    Central Files, 700.5/2–359. It is printed in volume VII, Part 2, <ref
                        target="frus1958-60v07p2#d93">Document 93</ref>.</p>
            </div>
